# Thunderstorm Breaking — Isolated Replicas of Features

When planning or performing work that replicates functionality from the Thunderstorm monolith into a standalone library, follow this rule. **We do not remove code from the monolith** — we create an **isolated replica** (a copy in a new library that does not depend on `@nu-art/thunderstorm-*`). The monolith stays as-is. Use the checklists below and update them as work completes.

## What Thunderstorm Is

**Thunderstorm** is the legacy monolithic core that provides shared backend (Storm, HTTP server, typed API, DB base modules), frontend (UI components, editable items, sync clients), and shared types/APIs. It is published as three tightly coupled packages:

- `@nu-art/thunderstorm-backend`
- `@nu-art/thunderstorm-frontend`
- `@nu-art/thunderstorm-shared`

Project policy (see how-we-work): **do not add new imports from `@nu-art/thunderstorm-*`**. When a feature must use something that currently lives in Thunderstorm, the goal is to create an **isolated replica** of that feature in a new standalone library that depends only on infra (e.g. `@nu-art/http-*`, `@nu-art/db-api-*`, `@nu-art/ts-common`, `@nu-art/firebase-*`). The original code remains in the monolith; we do not remove it.

## Thunderstorm Monolith — Tangled Domains

The Thunderstorm library contains many intertwined features. Use `_thunderstorm/thunderstorm/feature-list-and-dependency-graph.md` as the source of truth for the full list and dependency graph. Summary of main domains:

**Core / platform (BE):** ModuleBE_APIs, typed-api (createBodyServerApi, createQueryServerApi), HttpServer (server-api, route-resolvers, HeaderKey), Storm / BaseStorm, db-def.

**db-api-gen (BE):** ModuleBE_BaseDB, ModuleBE_BaseApi.

**Sync:** ModuleBE_SyncManager, ModuleFE_SyncManager, sync-manager shared; ModuleBE_SyncEnv, ModuleFE_SyncEnvV2, sync-env shared.

**Backup:** ModuleBE_BackupDocDB, ModuleBE_BackupScheduler.

**Collection actions:** ModuleBE_CollectionActions, dispatcher, ModuleFE_CollectionActions, collection-actions shared.

**Archiving:** ModuleBE_Archiving, ModuleFE_Archiving, archiving shared.

**Action processor:** ModuleBE_ActionProcessor, ModuleFE_ActionProcessor, action-processor shared.

**Entities / app support:** app-config (ModuleBE_AppConfigDB/API, ModuleFE_AppConfig), editable-test, backup-doc, deleted-doc; server-info, force-upgrade, cleanup-scheduler; BaseHttpModule, BaseHttpRequest, route-tools, headers, no-auth-listener.

**Frontend:** EditableItem / EditableDBItemV3, TS_InputV2, TS_TextAreaV2, TS_DropDown, adapter, and many UI components under `thunderstorm/frontend/`.

## Goal

Create **smaller libraries per feature as isolated replicas** so that:

- New and existing apps can depend on focused capability packages (e.g. sync-manager, archiving, editable-item) instead of the whole Thunderstorm monolith.
- Replica libraries **MUST NOT** depend on `@nu-art/thunderstorm-*`; they use `@nu-art/http-*`, `@nu-art/db-api-*`, `@nu-art/ts-common`, `@nu-art/firebase-*`, etc., as appropriate.
- The monolith is **not modified**; we copy and adapt, we do not remove.

