## How to Create an Isolated Replica of a Feature

1. **Map domains** — Identify which feature(s) you are replicating and which Thunderstorm domains they touch (backend, frontend, shared).
2. **Map main files** — List the main files/modules needed from each domain (use `feature-list-and-dependency-graph.md` and the codebase).
3. **Map Thunderstorm utils** — List any utility or type from Thunderstorm that the feature uses (directly or transitively).
4. **Map non-Thunderstorm deps** — List dependencies on other packages (ts-common, firebase, http, db-api, etc.).
5. **Create library structure** — Create the new concept library and package skeleton (shared/backend/frontend) per project structure and package-standard.
6. **Copy main files** — Copy (then adapt) the main feature files into the new library. **Do not remove or change the originals in the monolith.**
7. **Handle Thunderstorm utils** — For utilities that the feature uses and that live in Thunderstorm:
   - Prefer: depend on infra that already provides the capability (e.g. http, db-api).
   - If the utility is small and self-contained: **shallow copy** its functionality into the new library so the new library does not depend on `@nu-art/thunderstorm-*`.
   - If the utility is large or has many callers: **stop and discuss** with the user before duplicating or introducing a new shared package.
8. **Other packages** — For utilities from non-Thunderstorm packages, use them as-is (add the correct dependency to the new library).

## Checklist: How to create an isolated replica (per feature)

Use this when creating a replica of one of the features above.

- [ ] **Map domains** — Which feature(s); which Thunderstorm domains (backend, frontend, shared)
- [ ] **Map main files** — Main files/modules from each domain (use feature-list-and-dependency-graph.md)
- [ ] **Map Thunderstorm utils** — Utils/types from Thunderstorm used (directly or transitively)
- [ ] **Map non-Thunderstorm deps** — ts-common, firebase, http, db-api, etc.
- [ ] **Decide coupling** — Use existing lib, stub, shallow copy, inline, or replicate two features together (see todo.md “How we handle”)
- [ ] **Create library structure** — New concept library + package skeleton (shared/backend/frontend) per package-standard
- [ ] **Copy main files** — Copy (do not remove from monolith) then adapt into the new library
- [ ] **Handle Thunderstorm utils** — Prefer infra (http, db-api); else shallow copy if small; if large → stop and discuss
- [ ] **Other packages** — Use as-is; add correct dependency to new library
- [ ] **Tests** — Move existing Thunderstorm tests into new library; add/expand tests (package-standard tests rules); if no tests exists, create tests coverage
- [ ] **DoD** — Library has no `@nu-art/thunderstorm-*`; all packages compile; all tests pass (`bai -t -tt=... -up=<packages-regexp>`)

## Tests

- If the feature already has tests in Thunderstorm, **copy/replicate them** into the new library’s packages (monolith keeps its tests).
- Add or extend tests so that the new library has **covered test functionality** where appropriate (see package-standard tests rules).

## Definition of Done

- An **isolated replica** of the feature lives in a **standalone library** that **does not** depend on `@nu-art/thunderstorm-*`. (The monolith is unchanged.)
- All packages in that library **compile** (build with BAI).
- All tests in all packages of that library **pass** (`bai -t -tt=... -up=<packages-regexp>`).

**Per-feature checklist:**

- [ ] Isolated replica in a **standalone library** with **no** `@nu-art/thunderstorm-*` dependency; monolith not modified
- [ ] All packages in that library **compile** (BAI build)
- [ ] All tests in that library **pass**

Refer to `_thunderstorm/thunderstorm/feature-list-and-dependency-graph.md` and `_thunderstorm/thunderstorm/todo.md` for current replication plans and dependency details.
